his is what i'm thinking:<br>I spec in healing, my heals are great! i get the best res spell, my buffing is average.<br>I spec in buffing, my heals are ineffective, i only have the second rez spell, i can buff only an additional 30 points above what a healing specced druid can do.<br><br>If anyone has any input like, what types of druids are needed up at the high levels i'd appreciate that, or any feedback on my situation would also be greatly appreciated.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucloudien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cloudien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/3/02 2:01:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=282.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cloudk.clara.net/storage/zidane2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on how to spec</span><hr size=1> Just a newbie myself, so just IMO.  But I'd be tempted to spec about equal in healing and buffing.  Remember, even if some buffs are broken, Mythic do look at these things.  It'd be a real shame if you fully specced in healing, then they decided to greatly improve buffs.  <br><br>Like has been said, you get diminishing returns for points later on.  The difference between 40 and 50 isn't always that big (apparently).  Like with the res, the difference between 75% and 100% may not be that worth it, compared with some of the nice buffs you'd miss out on. <p>-- <br>Golsec the Champion, Hibernia<br>Cloudien the Druid, Hibernia<br>Excalubur(UK) server, Dark Ages of Camelot<br><A HREF="http://www.ceruleanstudios.com/forums/member.php?s=&action=aimmessage&aim=DerykAIM"><IMG SRC="http://superweb.yi.org:81/aim/DerykAIM"border="0"></a>  <A HREF="http://wwp.icq.com/25869912"><IMG SRC=